{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-19T21:52:15.232Z","tool_name":"run_shell_command","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1776635535232_0","parameters":{"command":"cat > code/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Cloned Repositories\n\nThis directory contains key codebases for text steganography with LLMs.\n\n## 1. Text-Steganography-Benchmark\n- **URL**: https://github.com/redwoodresearch/Text-Steganography-Benchmark\n- **Purpose**: A comprehensive benchmark for evaluating text steganography. Includes implementations of various methods and evaluation metrics.\n- **Key Files**:\n  - `steganography/`: Source code for steganography implementations.\n  - `scripts/`: Benchmark running scripts.\n- **Notes**: Developed by Redwood Research, it's a very solid baseline for evaluations.\n\n## 2. LLM-Steganography\n- **URL**: https://github.com/HighDoping/LLM-Steganography\n- **Purpose**: Official implementation for the paper \"Generative Text Steganography with Large Language Model\" (2024).\n- **Key Files**:\n  - `llm_stega/`: Core logic for LLM-based steganography.\n- **Notes**: Useful for modern black-box LLM steganography.\n\n## 3. TrojanStego\n- **URL**: https://github.com/worta/TrojanStego\n- **Purpose**: Implementation related to the \"TrojanStego\" attack mentioned in recent literature (Meier et al., 2025).\n- **Key Files**:\n  - `trojan_stego/`: Implementation of the bit-bucket attack.\n- **Notes**: Essential for studying persistent, fine-tuning-based steganographic attacks.\n\nEOF\n","description":"Create code/README.md."}}
